<div style=3D"margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0"><span lang=3D"en-US" style=3D"=
color:rgb(0,111,201)"><span style=3D"text-decoration:underline; color:rgb(0=
,111,201)"><strong style=3D"color:rgb(0,111,201); text-decoration:underline=
"><span style=3D"color:rgb(0,111,201); text-decoration:underline">Shale
 Oil and Gas: Process, Risks and Rewards</span></strong></span></span></div=
>
<div style=3D"margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0"><span lang=3D"en-US">Shale oil=
 and gas have changed the economic landscape in the US.</span><span lang=3D=
"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Shale oil has been responsible for the worldwid=
e plummet in oil and LNG prices.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">The political balance of energy power has shift=
ed. Geological considerations dictate that the resource is widely available=
 outside the US.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">The environmental risks can be managed with pro=
per regulations and associated practices.
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Properly cons=
tructed fiscal regimes will be critical for success.</span></div>
<div style=3D"margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0"><br>
<strong></strong></div>
<div style=3D"margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0"><span lang=3D"en-US" style=3D"=
color:rgb(0,111,201)"><span style=3D"text-decoration:underline; color:rgb(0=
,111,201)"><strong style=3D"color:rgb(0,111,201); text-decoration:underline=
"><span style=3D"color:rgb(0,111,201); text-decoration:underline">Strategie=
s
 for Displacing Oil</span></strong></span></span></div>
<div style=3D"margin-top:0; margin-bottom:0"><span lang=3D"en-US">Oil domin=
ates the transportation fuel sector.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Net importing nations would do well to develop =
strategies to displace oil to the extent feasible.</span><span lang=3D"en-U=
S">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Methanol and dimethyl ether (DME) are effective=
 partial or full substitutes for petrol and diesel, respectively.</span><sp=
an lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Both may be synthesized from either coal, natur=
al gas or biogas.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Each has much lower emissions than what it is r=
eplacing.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">DME has zero particulates in the discharge.</sp=
an><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Plummeting costs of DNA sequencing suggest that=
 the time is right for genetically modified Jatropha.</span><span lang=3D"e=
n-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Electric vehicles consume 60% less energy on a =
mine-to-wheel basis.</span><span lang=3D"en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">Widespread adoption likely requires a 50% drop =
in battery costs, but this is likely with a few years.</span><span lang=3D"=
en-US">&nbsp;
</span><span lang=3D"en-US">The goal is not to eliminate oil, it is to redu=
ce it from the position of a strategic commodity to a merely useful one.</s=
pan></div>
